<a class="definition-word" data-category="general-biology" id="agar">Agar</a> - Agar, not to be confused with <a href="#agarose">agarose</a> is a jelly like substance extracted from red algae known as <a href="#agarophytes">agarophytes</a> in the <a href="#rhodophyta">Rhodophyta</a> <a href="#phylum">phylum</a>. Agar is a mixture composed of about 30% <a href="#agaropectin">agaropectin</a> and 70% <a href="#agarose">agarose</a> (used in <a href="#electrophoresis">electrophoretic gels</a>). Agar is used as a solid medium for microbiology.